text: "\n <div id=\"recipeLeftColumn\">\n  # Pi Aloud\n  <hr/>\n  <img src=\"./piAloud.png\"\
  />\n  <div id=\"recipeGoal\">\n   ## Goal:\n   Use charAt and length methods to\
  \ access the digits of pi in a String variable.\n  </div>\n </div>\n <div id=\"\
  recipeRightColumn\">\n  <div id=\"recipeSteps\">\n   ## Steps:\n   <ol id=\"stepList\"\
  >\n    <li>\n     Place the first 20 digits of pi into a String variable.\n    </li>\n\
  \    <li>\n     Print out the first 3 digits of pi. Remember the first digit will\
  \ be pi.charAt(0).\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     Use a for loop to print each digit\
  \ of pi on a new line.\n    </li>\n    <li>\n     If your computer can play sounds,\
  \ use the speak method to say each digit of pi using a loop.\n    </li>\n    <li>\n\
  \     [CHALLENGE]\n     After printing the first 3 digits of pi, ask the user for\
  \ the next digit using the getInputFromUser() method\n     Compare the users' char\
  \ to the next digit of pi\n     If they are correct, print out \"correct\". If they\
  \ are not, print \"incorrect\"\n    </li>\n   </ol>\n  </div>\n </div>\n\n"
